<P>YOU are to go down to Brenton's Ford, hand captain Eccle&s;ton the letter which you carry down directed to him, after which you are to take charge of your guard which you marched down this morning, agreeable to the general order i&s;&s;ued expre&s;sly for the purpo&s;e of relieving captain Eccle|&s;ton and the other captains on piquet, which was founded unavoidably from the &s;carcity of officers not admitting of any other relief, and di&s;po&s;e of the centries in the be&s;t manner for the &s;ecurity of the Ford and po&s;t.</P>
