<DATE>May 31, 1778.</DATE></DATELINE></OPENER>
<P>Mr. NORWOOD, late a captain in the fourth Ma|ryland regiment, would be glad general Smallwood would &s;end him the charge on which he was arre&s;ted, as he does not know any conduct of his for which he ought to be con|fined or put under an arre&s;t.</P>
